SIMPLE: imputable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imputable
<hw>Im*put"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>imputable</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>That may be imputed; capable of being imputed;
chargeable; ascribable; attributable; referable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A prince whose political vices, at least, were
<qex>imputable</qex> to mental incapacity.</q>
<rj><qau>Prescott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Accusable; culpable.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The fault lies at his door, and she is no wise
<qex>imputable</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Ayliffe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imputableness</ent>⟦br⟧
